18#include "LuminanceSource.h"
19#include "ByteArray.h"
20
21#include <stdexcept>
22#include <algorithm>
23#include <utility>
24
25namespace ZXing {
26
27namespace {
28
29/**
30* A wrapper implementation of {@link LuminanceSource} which inverts the luminances it returns -- black becomes
31* white and vice versa, and each value becomes (255-value).
32*
33* @author Sean Owen
34*/
35class InvertedLuminanceSource : public LuminanceSource
36{
37 std::shared_ptr<LuminanceSource> _src;
38
39public:
40 explicit InvertedLuminanceSource(std::shared_ptr<LuminanceSource> src) : _src(std::move(src)) {}
41
42 const uint8_t* getRow(int y, ByteArray& outBytes, bool) const override
43 {
44 _src->getRow(y, outBytes, true);
45 std::transform(outBytes.begin(), outBytes.end(), outBytes.begin(), [](uint8_t b) { return 255 - b; });
46 return outBytes.data();
47 }
48
49 const uint8_t* getMatrix(ByteArray& outBytes, int& outRowBytes, bool) const override
50 {
51 _src->getMatrix(outBytes, outRowBytes, true);
52 std::transform(outBytes.begin(), outBytes.end(), outBytes.begin(), [](uint8_t b) { return 255 - b; });
53 return outBytes.data();
54 }
55
56 int width() const override
57 {
58 return _src->width();
59 }
60
61 /**
62 * @return The height of the bitmap.
63 */
64 int height() const override
65 {
66 return _src->height();
67 }
68
69 bool canCrop() const override
70 {
71 return _src->canCrop();
72 }
73
74 std::shared_ptr<LuminanceSource> cropped(int left, int top, int width, int height) const override
75 {
76 return CreateInverted(_src->cropped(left, top, width, height));
77 }
78
79 bool canRotate() const override
80 {
81 return _src->canRotate();
82 }
83
84 std::shared_ptr<LuminanceSource> rotated(int degreeCW) const override
85 {
86 return CreateInverted(_src->rotated(degreeCW));
87 }
88
89protected:
90 std::shared_ptr<LuminanceSource> getInverted() const override
91 {
92 return _src;
93 }
94
95}; // InvertedLuminanceSource
96
97} // anonymous
98
99
100bool
101LuminanceSource::canCrop() const
102{
103 return false;
104}
105
106std::shared_ptr<LuminanceSource>
107LuminanceSource::cropped(int, int, int, int) const
108{
109 throw std::runtime_error("This luminance source does not support cropping.");
110}
111
112bool
113LuminanceSource::canRotate() const
114{
115 return false;
116}
117
118/**
119* Returns a new object with rotated image data by 90 degrees counterclockwise.
120* Only callable if {@link #isRotateSupported()} is true.
121*
122* @return A rotated version of this object.
123*/
124std::shared_ptr<LuminanceSource>
125LuminanceSource::rotated(int) const
126{
127 throw std::runtime_error("This luminance source does not support rotation by 90 degrees.");
128}
129
130std::shared_ptr<LuminanceSource>
131LuminanceSource::getInverted() const
132{
133 return nullptr;
134}
135
136std::shared_ptr<LuminanceSource>
137LuminanceSource::CreateInverted(const std::shared_ptr<LuminanceSource>& src)
138{
139 auto result = src->getInverted();
140 if (result == nullptr)
141 result = std::make_shared<InvertedLuminanceSource>(src);
142 return result;
143}
